    <div id="entry-308">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="http://www.encs.concordia.ca/news-and-events/entry.php?a=2011/02/ashrae-comes-to-concordia.php">ASHRAE comes to Concordia</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2011-02-14T13:57:48-05:00">Monday Feb 14, 2011
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			On Tuesday, February 8, the Montreal Chapter of the <a href="http://www.ashrae.org/">American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air-Conditioning Engineers</a> (ASHRAE), held its career fair here at Concordia University. The annual event gave industry leaders the chance to discuss future employment opportunities with engineering students from across the province. <br /><br /><object width="400" height="300"> <param name="flashvars" value="offsite=true&amp;lang=en-us&amp;page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157626048001098%2Fshow%2F&amp;page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157626048001098%2F&amp;set_id=72157626048001098&amp;jump_to=" /> <param name="movie" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" /> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" allowfullscreen="true" flashvars="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157626048001098%2Fshow%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157626048001098%2F&set_id=72157626048001098&jump_to=" width="400" height="300"></object><br /><br />Students from CEGEPS across Qu√©bec, as well as from l'√0cole de Technologie Sup√©rieur, l'√0cole Polytechnique de Montr√©al, and McGill University came to Concordia for an afternoon of meetings and greetings, followed by an evening of presentations and socialization. <br /><br />On-hand for the career fair portion of the gathering were industry leaders including: Gaz Metro, Cimco, Hydro Quebec, SNC Lavalin, Siemens Tech., Du Batiment, Honeywell, Preston Phipps, Bouthillette, Parizeau, Dupras Ledoux, Groupe S. M., Pageau Morel, Trane, Groupe Master, and Premieair. Exhibitors from these companies set up display booths in the atrium of the EV building and met with interested undergraduates, taking the time to explain what they're looking for in future employees.<br /><br />Once the exhibit wrapped up, industry representatives joined students upstairs for a special presentation by our own Andreas Athienitis, Director of the <a href="http://www.solarbuildings.ca/en/network">NSERC Solar Buildings Research Network</a>. He spoke about the innovative work that went into the design and construction of the unique solar wall on Concordia's John Molson School of Business building. Following the talk, students and professors joined industry reps for a special reception that gave everyone the chance to mingle in an informal atmosphere. Ronald Gagnon, President of ASHRAE Montreal, joined Hydro Qu√©bec's Andr√© Labont√© (who is also a member of the Chapter's Technology Transfer Committee) to address the crowd at the end of the night and offer their praise to Concordia's event organizers for a job well done. <br />
		</div>
	
	</div>
</div>
