    <div id="entry-294">
	<div class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="http://www.encs.concordia.ca/news-and-events/entry.php?a=2011/02/undergraduates-celebrated-in-annual-deans-awards-1.php">Undergraduates celebrated in annual Dean's Awards</a></h2>
		<div class="entry-meta" title="2011-02-02T14:28:32-05:00">Wednesday Feb  2, 2011
                </div>
	</div>

	<div class="entry-content">
	
		<div class="entry-body">
			On January 28, 2011, some of ENCS's brightest undergraduates were honoured at the annual Dean's Awards. The evening began with a special cocktail for award recipients in the second floor atrium, outside of the Dean's office. Award winners and honourees got the chance to mingle with each other, as well as with Faculty and staff members while having a drink and tucking into delicious canap√©s.<br /><br /><object width="400" height="300"> <param name="flashvars" value="offsite=true&amp;lang=en-us&amp;page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157625961999256%2Fshow%2F&amp;page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157625961999256%2F&amp;set_id=72157625961999256&amp;jump_to=" /> <param name="movie" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" /> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" allowfullscreen="true" flashvars="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157625961999256%2Fshow%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157625961999256%2F&set_id=72157625961999256&jump_to=" width="400" height="300"></object><br /><br />The awards ceremony was then held in the Normand D. H√©bert conference room in the EV building, and was MCed by Dr. Robin Drew, Dean of the Faculty of Engineering. Undergraduate students from the three tiers of the Dean's List of Excellence were presented with monetary awards and special gifts from the Faculty in honour of their excellent academic achievements. The Tier 1, 2, and 3 awards were handed out by Dr. William Lynch, Chair of the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering; Dr. Martin Pugh, Chair of the Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering; and Dr. Sudhir Mudur, Chair of the Department of Computer Science and Software Engineering. <br /><br /><div align="center"><img alt="medraj.jpg" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/medraj.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="margin: 0pt auto 20px; text-align: center; display: block;" width="440" height="400" /><i><font style="font-size: 0.8em;">Dean Robin Drew presents Professor Mahmoun Medraj with commemorative plaques</font></i><br /></div><br />Then it was time to switch from honouring students to honouring a very special faculty member, Dr. Mahmoun Medraj. Dr. Nancy Acemian, recipient of last year's Teaching Excellence Award, read out the citation for the Associate Professor of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering, noting that he "manages to awake the curiosity of his students." Dean Drew--who was Dr. Medraj's PhD supervisor--then presented him with two commemorative plaques, joking "I don't think he learned anything from me about teaching!"<br /><br /><div align="center"><img alt="carbone.jpg" src="http://newsfeed.encs.concordia.ca/encs_test/carbone.jpg" class="mt-image-center" style="margin: 0pt auto 20px; text-align: center; display: block;" width="440" height="375" /><i><font style="font-size: 0.8em;">Albert Carbone receives the Award of Distinction from Dean Robin Drew</font><br /></i></div><br />The next award presented was the Award of Distinction, which is given every year to a special alumnus or almuna in recognition of their innovative contributions to the community. This year's recipient was Albert Carbone, who was awarded his BEng in 1981 and his MEng 84. He was honoured to receive the award and spoke with great fondness of his time as a student here. He gave a succinct account of his rise in the business world, which culminated in the founding of <a href="http://www.stelvio.com/">Stelvio Inc</a>. in 1991, which has since grown to become a major multinational company. "I started out working for others," said Carbone in his inspirational speech to the assembled undergraduates, "and ended up working for myself." He then presented the Jaan Saber and Phoivos Ziogas Memorial Scholarships, as well as the Stelvio Software Engineering Excellence Scholarship--endowed scholarships which he founded himself and through his company.<br /><br />The focus then turned to the other student awards of the night, which included the Normand D. H√©bert Engineering Scholarship, The Memorial Endowment Entrance Scholarship, The Groupe LGS Inc. Scholarships in Engineering, The Aaron M. Fish Scholarship of Excellence in Mechanical Engineering, Bourses d'√©tudes Hydro-Qu√©bec de l'universit√© Concordia, The Faculty of Engineering &amp; Computer Science Distinguished CEGEP Entrance Scholarship, Association des ing√©nieurs-conseils du Qu√©bec - AICQ, and the Leadership Excellence Awards.<br /><br />To see a full photo gallery of the event, be sure to <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/encs-concordia/sets/72157625961999256/">view the set on Flickr</a>.<br /><br /><a href="../../documents/ENCS_DeanList_2009-10.pdf">Download the list of award recipients</a>.<br /><div><br /></div>
		</div>
	
	</div>
</div>
